title: Dez Bryant did not fly with Cowboys to New York Friday

WFAA.com: http://on.wfaa.com/1LTcZwk   Join the Conversation To   Dez Bryant did not fly with Cowboys to New York Friday Landon Haaf, WFAA Sports 7:47 p.m. CDT October 23, 2015 Dez Bryant CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Cowboys wide receiver Dez Bryant did not travel with the team to New York Friday, WFAA Sports confirmed. 
According our media partners at the Star-Telegram, Bryant was spending Friday night resting at home and would make the decision whether to fly up Saturday. 
Bryant missed practice each day this week ahead of the Cowboys’ Week 7 game against the Giants. He is officially listed as doubtful for Sunday's game. 
The star wideout hasn’t played since breaking his foot in the first game of the year -- also against the Giants. #Cowboys WR Dez Bryant listed as doubtful after did not practice. Missed every practice for #Giants . Jason Garrett said practice a must. — Ed Werder (@Edwerderespn) October 23, 2015 
Executive vice president Stephen Jones said Friday on 105.3 The Fan that Bryant has “some work to do” if he's going to suit up Sunday. 
“We want to make sure we make the right call,” Jones said . 
The Cowboys flew to New York a day early to visit Ground Zero. Dez Bryant did not travel with the #Cowboys to NY today. He's resting at home. The possibility does exist that he'll fly to NY on Saturday.
